	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=212275><span id= >rusrec</span></a><br><span id=notbold>2 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>I believe a loom is inside the silk underground, behind the merchants there.&nbsp;&nbsp;I also opted to get small sewing kit, because you can just carry it around with you (btw it will hold two patterns and you can just exchange your fused hide for one and combine, then do same for other).  This keeps the trips throught the annoyingly segmented town of nierak to a minimum.  After MANY hours of frustration looking for scout scalps I gave up.  &quot;Was hampering the fun factor severely&quot;.  I did however make all the items that did not require scalps and they are nice for a lower lvl necro to have, so if you get lucky and find one do yourself a favor and make the darned thing, if only to make everyone else jealous. lol.  Really though, after so long I just deternimed that it wasnt worth it to keep pounding away on deathfists.  If you get it good.  If not after a few hours move on.<br><br>lvl 12 DEF/NEC &quot;Vileness&quot; - Tunare</p>&nbsp;<br>24 IKS/BST Rusrec - Terris-Thule<br>17 DEF/NEC Vileness<br>Tunare server<br>12 DEF/NEC Vileness - Tunare</td></td></tr>
